The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Student body elections will be held at Bengal Engineering and Science University after three years on Tuesday. Around 1,600 undergraduate students will vote to select 53 representatives. Around 400 postgraduate students will select 45 representatives. Over 100 policemen will be deployed on the Shibpur campus.    Two-year-old Reshmi Khatoon was mowed down by a truck on Strand Bank Road, near Jyoti Nagar colony, on Monday. Police said the girl was playing on the road when the vehicle hit her. The driver was arrested.    Singapore Airlines has announced promotional fares of Rs 16,830 to Singapore and Rs 23,980 to Kuala Lumpur, Penang, Bangkok, Denpasar, Langkawi and Kuching. Bookings can be made till January 15, 2009. The fares are inclusive of all taxes, said an airline official.    Sheikh Hossain was hit by a bullet on his right arm during a gang fight on Tiljala Road early on Monday. Police said the clash broke out over a plot of land.                                                                                                                                                              
